24/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Ion Iliescu presented outgoing US Ambassador Michael Guest with the Trustful Service National Order during a ceremony at the Cotroceni Palace on Wednesday (23 June).
Iliescu cited Guest's constant efforts to enhance Romanian-American relations and his contributions to Romania's NATO integration.
In other news, local media reported Wednesday that European Commissioner for Enlargement Guenter Verheugen says the scope of reforms Romania must complete may delay EU accession until 2008.
Romania hopes to join the Union in 2007 with Bulgaria, but must still close several chapters in its accession talks.
(Rompres - 24/06/04;
Mediafax, UPI - 23/06/04)
